===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An establishment that [[sell]]s goods to the public; originally a physical location, but now a virtual establishment as well.
# A place where things are [[craft]]ed, a [[workshop]] or [[hobbyshop]].
# An [[automobile]] [[machanic]]'s workplace.
# [[workplace|Workplace]]; [[office]]. Used mainly in expressions such as ''[[shop talk]]'', ''[[closed shop]]'' and ''[[shop floor]]''.
# Short for ''[[wood shop]]'', a class taught typically in junior high school, teaching vocational skill. Also ''[[metal shop]]'' could be shortened this way.
# Something resembling a shop or the practise of a shop, e.g. to live above your office is 'to live above the shop'. Also in the phrase 'coffee shop', 'chip shop' etc.
# The act of betrayal.

